contentrichtext.text: {{MedalTableTop}} {{MedalSport | Women's [[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Archery]]}} {{MedalCompetition | [[Asian Games]]}} {{MedalSilver | [[2006 Asian Games|2006 Doha]] | Team }} {{MedalBottom}} '''Qian Jialing''' (born February 3, 1988) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] [[archery|archer]] and is a [[World Archery Rankings#Number one ranked archers|former world number one]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/sports/2006-12/11/content_755242.htm|title=NO.1 archer ousted due to rule|date=2006-12-11|publisher=Xinhua|accessdate=23 January 2010}}</ref> She won the silver medal in the team competition at the [[2006 Asian Games]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaenews.com/middle-east/20061214/32433.htm|title=South Koreans sweep archery titles, India wins bronze|date=2006-12-14|publisher=India eNews|accessdate=23 January 2010}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}} {{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. --> | NAME = Qian Jialing | ALTERNATIVE NAMES = | SHORT DESCRIPTION = Chinese archer | DATE OF BIRTH = February 3, 1988 | PLACE OF BIRTH = | DATE OF DEATH = | PLACE OF DEATH = }} {{DEFAULTSORT:Qian Jialing}} [[Category:Living people]] [[Category:1988 births]] [[Category:Chinese archers]] [[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]] [[Category:Asian Games medalists in archery]] {{PRChina-archery-bio-stub}}
